Target levels for LDL cholesterol by NCEP guidelines depend on the number of major risk factors: <100mg/dL for patients with diabetes or CHD. <130mg/dL for patients with 2 or more risk factors excluding diabetes and CHD. <160mg/dL for patients with <2 major risk factors.
